sentences: GDP began in 2008 with the release of a split with Dirty Money.
The following year he released his debut full-length album, titled Realistic Expectations via Say-10 Records.
In 2010, GDP released his first cassette titled Magic Bullet via Ride
In 2011, GDP released his second full-length album titled Useless Eaters via Run For Cover Records.
In 2013, GDP released a Vinyl with The Wrong Address, titled Holla via Run For Cover.
In 2014, GDP released a compilation album titled Collectibles via Smokers Cough and Ride The Fury.
In March 2014, The Front Bottoms announced at the South by Southwest music festival plans to release a split with GDP sometime in the future.
